Date of Birth: June 24, 1804<br/>
Birthplace: Hopkinton, Massachusetts, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 14, 1840<br/>
Death: March 11, 1854<br/>
<br/>
Born June 24, 1804, at Hopkinton, Middlesex Co., Massachusetts, to Joseph Richards and Rhoda Howe.
Ordained apostle April 14, 1840, by Brigham Young, at age 35;
sustained as second counselor to President Young Dec. 27, 1847, at age 43;
died March 11, 1854, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 49.